FILLER.Name: ssl_renegotiation_limit
FILLER.Desc: amount of data between renegotiations

FILLER.Name: tcp_keepalives_idle
FILLER.Desc: TCP_KEEPIDLE, in seconds; 0 selects the system default

FILLER.Name: tcp_keepalives_interval
FILLER.Desc: TCP_KEEPINTVL, in seconds; 0 selects the system default

FILLER.Name: tcp_keepalives_count
FILLER.Desc: Specifies the number of keepalive packets to send on an otherwise idle connection. A value of 0 uses the system default. This parameter is supported only on systems that support TCP_KEEPCNT or an equivalent socket option; on other systems, it must be zero. In sessions connected via a Unix-domain socket, this parameter is ignored and always reads as zero.

FILLER.Name: temp_buffers
FILLER.Desc: Sets the maximum number of temporary buffers used by each database session. These are session-local buffers used only for access to temporary tables. The default is eight megabytes (8MB).

FILLER.Name: max_prepared_transactions
FILLER.Desc: Sets the maximum number of transactions that can be in the “prepared” state simultaneously. Setting this parameter to zero (which is the default) disables the prepared-transaction feature.

FILLER.Name: work_mem
FILLER.Desc: Specifies the amount of memory to be used by internal sort operations and hash tables beforewriting to temporary disk files. The value defaults to one megabyte (1MB).

FILLER.Name: maintenance_work_mem
FILLER.Desc: Specifies the maximum amount of memory to be used by maintenance operations, such as VACUUM, CREATE INDEX, and ALTER TABLE ADD FOREIGN KEY. It defaults to 16 megabytes (16MB).

FILLER.Name: max_stack_depth
FILLER.Desc: Specifies the maximum safe depth of the server’s execution stack. The default setting is two megabytes (2MB).

FILLER.Name: temp_file_limit
FILLER.Desc: limits per-session temp file space in kB, or -1 for no limit

FILLER.Name: max_files_per_process
FILLER.Desc: Sets the maximum number of simultaneously open files allowed to each server subprocess. The default is one thousand files.

FILLER.Name: shared_preload_libraries
FILLER.Desc: This variable specifies one or more shared libraries to be preloaded at server start.

FILLER.Name: vacuum_cost_delay
FILLER.Desc: The length of time, in milliseconds, that the process will sleep when the cost limit has been exceeded. The default value is zero.

FILLER.Name: vacuum_cost_page_hit
FILLER.Desc: The estimated cost for vacuuming a buffer found in the shared buffer cache. It represents the cost to lock the buffer pool, lookup the shared hash table and scan the content of the page. The default value is one

FILLER.Name: vacuum_cost_page_miss
FILLER.Desc: The estimated cost for vacuuming a buffer that has to be read from disk. This represents the effort to lock the buffer pool, lookup the shared hash table, read the desired block in from the disk and scan its content. The default value is 10.

FILLER.Name: vacuum_cost_page_dirty
FILLER.Desc: The estimated cost charged when vacuum modifies a block that was previously clean. It represents the extra I/O required to flush the dirty block out to disk again. The default value is 20.

FILLER.Name: vacuum_cost_limit
FILLER.Desc: The accumulated cost that will cause the vacuuming process to sleep. The default value is 200

FILLER.Name: bgwriter_delay
FILLER.Desc: Specifies the delay between activity rounds for the background writer.The default value is 200 milliseconds (200ms).

FILLER.Name: bgwriter_lru_maxpages
FILLER.Desc: In each round, no more than this many buffers will be written by the background writer. Setting this to zero disables background writing. The default value is 100 buffers.

FILLER.Name: bgwriter_lru_multiplier
FILLER.Desc: The number of dirty buffers written in each round is based on the number of new buffers that have been needed by server processes during recent rounds.The default is 2.0.

FILLER.Name: effective_io_concurrency
FILLER.Desc: Sets the number of concurrent disk I/O operations that PostgreSQL expects can be executed simultaneously. The allowed range is 1 to 1000, or zero to disable issuance of asynchronous I/O requests.

FILLER.Name: fsync
FILLER.Desc: turns forced synchronization on or off

FILLER.Name: wal_buffers
FILLER.Desc: min 32kB,select -1 sets based on shared_buffers

FILLER.Name: wal_writer_delay
FILLER.Desc: Range is 1-10000 milliseconds, The default value is 200 milliseconds

FILLER.Name: commit_delay
FILLER.Desc: range 0-100000, default is 0

FILLER.Name: commit_siblings
FILLER.Desc: Minimum number of concurrent open transactions to require before performing the commit_delay delay. A larger value makes it more probable that at least one other transaction will become ready to commit during the delay interval. The default is five transactions.

FILLER.Name: checkpoint_segments
FILLER.Desc: Maximum number of log file segments between automatic WAL checkpoints (each segment is normally 16 megabytes). The default is three segments. Increasing this parameter can increase the amount of time needed for crash recovery.

FILLER.Name: checkpoint_timeout
FILLER.Desc: Maximum time between automatic WAL checkpoints, in seconds. The default is five minutes (5min).

FILLER.Name: checkpoint_completion_target
FILLER.Desc: Specifies the target of checkpoint completion, as a fraction of total time between checkpoints. The default is 0.5.

FILLER.Name: checkpoint_warning
FILLER.Desc: Write a message to the server log if checkpoints caused by the filling of checkpoint segment files happen closer together than this many seconds (which suggests that checkpoint_segments ought to be raised). The default is 30 seconds (30s).

FILLER.Name: archive_mode
FILLER.Desc: allows archiving to be done

FILLER.Name: archive_command
FILLER.Desc: The shell command to execute to archive a completed WAL file segment. Any %p in the string is replaced by the path name of the file to archive, and any %f is replaced by only the file name. Use %% to embed an actual % character in the command.

FILLER.Name: archive_timeout
FILLER.Desc: number of seconds; 0 disables

FILLER.Name: max_wal_senders
FILLER.Desc: max number of walsender processes

FILLER.Name: wal_keep_segments
FILLER.Desc: in logfile segments, 16MB each; 0 disables

FILLER.Name: wal_sender_timeout
FILLER.Desc: in milliseconds; 0 disables

FILLER.Name: synchronous_standby_names
FILLER.Desc: Specifies a comma-separated list of standby names that can support synchronous replication.

FILLER.Name: vacuum_defer_cleanup_age
FILLER.Desc: Specifies the number of transactions by which VACUUM and HOT updates will defer cleanup of dead row versions. The default is zero transactions.

FILLER.Name: hot_standby
FILLER.Desc: select "on" allows queries during recovery

FILLER.Name: max_standby_archive_delay
FILLER.Desc: max delay before canceling queries when reading WAL from archive; -1 allows indefinite delay

FILLER.Name: max_standby_streaming_delay
FILLER.Desc: max delay before canceling queries when reading streaming WAL; -1 allows indefinite delay

FILLER.Name: wal_receiver_status_interval
FILLER.Desc: send replies at least this often; 0 disables

FILLER.Name: hot_standby_feedback
FILLER.Desc: send info from standby to prevent query conflicts

FILLER.Name: wal_receiver_timeout
FILLER.Desc: time that receiver waits for communication from master in milliseconds; 0 disables

FILLER.Name: enable_bitmapscan
FILLER.Desc: Enables or disables the query planner’s use of bitmap-scan plan types. The default is on.

FILLER.Name: enable_hashagg
FILLER.Desc: Enables or disables the query planner’s use of hashed aggregation plan types. The default is on.

FILLER.Name: enable_hashjoin
FILLER.Desc: Enables or disables the query planner’s use of hash-join plan types. The default is on.

FILLER.Name: enable_indexscan
FILLER.Desc: Enables or disables the query planner’s use of index-scan plan types. The default is on.

FILLER.Name: enable_indexonlyscan
FILLER.Desc: Enables or disables the query planner’s use of index-only-scan plan types. The default is on

FILLER.Name: enable_material
FILLER.Desc: Enables or disables the query planner’s use of materialization. It is impossible to suppress materializationentirely, but turning this variable off prevents the planner from inserting materializenodes except in cases where it is required for correctness. The default is on.

FILLER.Name: enable_mergejoin
FILLER.Desc: Enables or disables the query planner’s use of merge-join plan types. The default is on

FILLER.Name: seq_page_cost
FILLER.Desc: Sets the planner’s estimate of the cost of a disk page fetch that is part of a series of sequential fetches. The default is 1.0.

FILLER.Name: random_page_cost
FILLER.Desc: Sets the planner’s estimate of the cost of a non-sequentially-fetched disk page. The default is 4.0.

FILLER.Name: cpu_tuple_cost
FILLER.Desc: Sets the planner’s estimate of the cost of processing each row during a query. The default is 0.01.

FILLER.Name: cpu_index_tuple_cost
FILLER.Desc: Sets the planner’s estimate of the cost of processing each index entry during an index scan. The default is 0.005.

FILLER.Name: cpu_operator_cost
FILLER.Desc: Sets the planner’s estimate of the cost of processing each operator or function executed during a query. The default is 0.0025.

FILLER.Name: geqo_effort
FILLER.Desc: Controls the trade-off between planning time and query plan quality in GEQO. This variable must be an integer in the range from 1 to 10. The default value is 5.

FILLER.Name: geqo_selection_bias
FILLER.Desc: Controls the selection bias used by GEQO. The selection bias is the selective pressure within the population. Values can be from 1.50 to 2.00; The default value is 2.

FILLER.Name: geqo_seed
FILLER.Desc: Controls the initial value of the random number generator used by GEQO to select random paths through the join order search space. The value can range from zero (the default) to one.

FILLER.Name: default_statistics_target
FILLER.Desc: Sets the default statistics target for table columns without a column-specific target set via ALTER TABLE SET STATISTICS. The default is 100.

FILLER.Name: cursor_tuple_fraction
FILLER.Desc: Sets the planner’s estimate of the fraction of a cursor’s rows that will be retrieved. The default is 0.1.

FILLER.Name: from_collapse_limit
FILLER.Desc: The planner will merge sub-queries into upper queries if the resulting FROM list would have no more than this many items. Smaller values reduce planning time but might yield inferior query plans. The default is 8.

FILLER.Name: join_collapse_limit
FILLER.Desc: The planner will rewrite explicit JOIN constructs (except FULL JOINs) into lists of FROM items whenever a list of no more than this many items would result. Smaller values reduce planning time but might yield inferior query plans.

FILLER.Name: log_destination
FILLER.Desc: PostgreSQL supports several methods for logging server messages, including stderr, csvlog and syslog. On Windows, eventlog is also supported. Set this parameter to a list of desired log desti470 Chapter 18. Server Configuration nations separated by commas. The default is to log to stderr only.

FILLER.Name: logging_collector
FILLER.Desc: Enable capturing of stderr and csvlog into log files. Required to be on for csvlogs

FILLER.Name: log_directory
FILLER.Desc: directory where log files are written, can be absolute or relative to PGDATA

FILLER.Name: log_filename
FILLER.Desc: When logging_collector is enabled, this parameter sets the file names of the created log files. The default is postgresql-%Y-%m-%d_%H%M%S.log.

FILLER.Name: log_file_mode
FILLER.Desc: creation mode for log files, begin with 0 to use octal notation

FILLER.Name: log_rotation_age
FILLER.Desc: Automatic rotation of logfiles will happen after that time. 0 disables.

FILLER.Name: log_rotation_size
FILLER.Desc: Automatic rotation of logfiles will happen after that much log output. 0 disables.

FILLER.Name: log_min_duration_statement
FILLER.Desc: -1 is disabled, 0 logs all statements and their durations, > 0 logs only statements running at least this number of milliseconds

FILLER.Name: log_line_prefix
log_lock_waits
FILLER.Desc: log lock waits >= deadlock_timeout

FILLER.Name: log_temp_files
FILLER.Desc: log temporary files equal or larger than the specified size in kilobytes; -1 disables, 0 logs all temp files

FILLER.Name: autovacuum
FILLER.Desc: Controls whether the server should run the autovacuum launcher daemon. This is on by default; however, track_counts must also be enabled for autovacuum to work.The default is on.

FILLER.Name: log_autovacuum_min_duration
FILLER.Desc: Causes each action executed by autovacuum to be logged if it ran for at least the specified number of milliseconds. Setting this to zero logs all autovacuum actions. The default is -1 disables logging autovacuum actions.

FILLER.Name: autovacuum_max_workers
FILLER.Desc: Specifies the maximum number of autovacuum processes (other than the autovacuum launcher) which may be running at any one time. The default is three.

FILLER.Name: autovacuum_naptime
FILLER.Desc: Specifies the minimum delay between autovacuum runs on any given database. In each round the daemon examines the database and issues VACUUM and ANALYZE commands as needed for tables in that database. The delay is measured in seconds, and the default is one minute (1min).

FILLER.Name: autovacuum_vacuum_threshold
FILLER.Desc: Specifies the minimum number of updated or deleted tuples needed to trigger a VACUUM in any one table. The default is 50 tuples.

FILLER.Name: autovacuum_analyze_threshold
FILLER.Desc: Specifies the minimum number of inserted, updated or deleted tuples needed to trigger an ANALYZE in any one table. The default is 50 tuples.

FILLER.Name: autovacuum_vacuum_scale_factor
FILLER.Desc: Specifies a fraction of the table size to add to autovacuum_vacuum_threshold when deciding whether to trigger a VACUUM. The default is 0.2 (20% of table size).

FILLER.Name: autovacuum_analyze_scale_factor
FILLER.Desc: Specifies a fraction of the table size to add to autovacuum_analyze_threshold when deciding whether to trigger an ANALYZE. The default is 0.1 (10% of table size).

FILLER.Name: autovacuum_freeze_max_age
FILLER.Desc: Specifies the maximum age (in transactions) that a table's pg_class.relfrozenxid field can attain before a VACUUM operation is forced to prevent transaction ID wraparound within the table. The default is 200000000.

FILLER.Name: autovacuum_multixact_freeze_max_age
FILLER.Desc: Specifies the maximum age (in multixacts) that a table’s pg_class.relminmxid field can attain before a VACUUM operation is forced to prevent multixact ID wraparound within the table. The default is 400000000.

FILLER.Name: autovacuum_vacuum_cost_delay
FILLER.Desc: Specifies the cost delay value that will be used in automatic VACUUM operations. If -1 is specified, the regular vacuum_cost_delay value will be used. The default value is 20 milliseconds.

FILLER.Name: autovacuum_vacuum_cost_limit
FILLER.Desc: Specifies the cost limit value that will be used in automatic VACUUM operations. If -1 is specified (which is the default), the regular vacuum_cost_limit value will be used.

FILLER.Name: default_tablespace
FILLER.Desc: This variable specifies the default tablespace in which to create objects (tables and indexes) when a CREATE command does not explicitly specify a tablespace. The default value is ''.

FILLER.Name: temp_tablespaces
FILLER.Desc: This variable specifies tablespaces in which to create temporary objects (temp tables and indexes on temp tables) when a CREATE command does not explicitly specify a tablespace. The default value is ''.
